# Prefer XDS components over raw HTML

The sandbox docsite should use XDS components for all layout and styling. Avoid raw `<div style>` wrappers.

## Page containers

```tsx
// BAD — raw div with inline styles
<div style={{maxWidth: 840, margin: '0 auto', padding: '32px 40px'}}>

// GOOD — XDS layout components
<XDSCenter axis="horizontal">
  <XDSSection maxWidth={840} padding={5} variant="transparent">
```

## Text with monospace

```tsx
// BAD — inline fontFamily override
<XDSText type="supporting" style={{fontFamily: 'monospace'}}>

// GOOD — use type="code"
<XDSText type="code" size="xs">
```

## Spacing between sections

```tsx
// BAD — div wrappers with marginTop
<div style={{marginTop: 40}}>
  <XDSHeading level={2}>Section</XDSHeading>
  ...
</div>

// GOOD — XDSStack with gap
<XDSStack direction="vertical" gap={10}>
  <XDSStack direction="vertical" gap={3}>
    <XDSHeading level={2}>Section</XDSHeading>
    ...
  </XDSStack>
</XDSStack>
```

## Colors

Use XDS color props instead of hardcoded values or CSS variable fallbacks.

```tsx
// BAD
<XDSText style={{color: 'var(--color-text-accent, #0066FF)'}}>

// GOOD
<XDSText color="active">
```
